snippet.statement:
Description: Verbalizes a conditional statement on two lines.
Format: if {0}
        then {1}

Description: Verbalizes a conditional statement on two lines with the 'then' line indented.
Format: if {0}
          then {1}

Description: Used to open a secondary error report. Secondary reports contain errors that do not block verbalization.
Replacement: {0}=error text,{1}=error id
Format: Model Error: {0}

Description: Used to verbalize a single primary error.
Replacement: {0}=error text,{1}=error id
Format: Model Error: {0}

Description: Verbalizes for each instance of an object, some rule applies to those instances.
Format positive: for each {0}, {1}
Format negative: for some {0}, {1}

Description: Verbalizes for each instance of an object then creates a line break where the rules that apply to those instances are listed.
Format positive: for each {0}, \n{1}
Format negative: for some {0}, \n{1}

Description: Relate two variables of different types that represent the same instance where the first
variable is an impersonal object type.
Format: {0} that is {1}

Description: Verbalizes that an object occurs at most once or more than once in a given population.
Format positive: in each population of {1}, {0} occurs at most once
Format negative: {0} occurs more than once in the same population of {1}

Description: Used for 'at most one' or 'more than one' before an object.
Format positive: at most one {0}
Format negative: more than one {0}

Description: Relate two variable names of different types that represent the same instance where the first
variable is a personal object type.
Format:  {0} who is {1}

